# module: eng.sampling
# status: native workflow support
# purpose: deterministic sample tables and design sweeps with units, constraints, seed policy, and reviewable metadata.
#
# Current implementation:
#   `sample grid`, `sample random`, and `sample lhs` produce deterministic
#   RuntimeTable records with generated `case_id` values, parameter columns,
#   seed metadata, and row hashes. Promoted CSV tables whose schema/source/
#   binding is sample-like also produce typed_payload.sample_tables[] entries
#   with sample count, case_id column, numeric parameter ranges, duplicate
#   case IDs, deterministic row-hash previews, and source hash.
#
# Helper vocabulary:
#   sample grid
#   sample random
#   sample lhs
#   uniform(lower, upper)
#
# Review contract:
#   parameter schema, ranges, seed when generated, sample count, sample row
#   hashes or hash previews, source hash, and diagnostics for duplicate or
#   invalid case IDs.
#
# Non-goal:
#   random sampling without an explicit seed must not pass repro review.
